  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Supply Chain Program Executive",
  "description": "<p>Duties and Responsibilities includes, but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Support end-to-end execution of Supply Chain programs – from demand planning, procurement, and logistics to customer delivery</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with cross-functional teams to meet project or program milestones</li>\n  <li>Track progress of program deliverables and proactively address Supply Chain risks or delays</li>\n  <li>Liaise with Suppliers to ensure timely material supply, order accuracy, and compliance with specifications</li>\n  <li>Work closely with Sales to manage delivery schedules, order status and program requirements</li>\n  <li>Performs Supplier qualification, onboarding and tracks performance monitoring</li>\n  <li>Maintain and update program dashboards, metrics and reports for management review</li>\n  <li>Analyse material flow, lead times, and cost performance to identify improvement opportunities</li>\n  <li>Prepare summaries on program health (inventory levels, shipment schedules, cost variance)</li>\n  <li>Plan and coordinate inbound and outbound shipments to ensure on-time delivery</li>\n  <li>Liaise with freight forwarders for import/export matters</li>\n  <li>Optimise transportation and warehouse operations for cost efficiency</li>\n  <li>Continuously improve Supply Chain visibility</li>\n  <li>Support continuous improvement initiatives across Supply Chain to enhance responsiveness and efficiency</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Supply Chain Management and at least 5 years’ experience in Supply Chain Program in similar industry</li>\n  <li>Familiar with import/export procedures and Incoterms</li>\n  <li>Chartered Institute of Procurement &amp; Supply (CIPS) or similar qualification</li>\n  <li>ERP and MRP knowledge is required</li>\n</ul>",
